    <preamble>
      <formula name="enactingFormula" eId="formula_1">
        <p xml:space="preserve">
          <span class="italic">The Security Council</span>,</p>
      </formula>
      <container name="Recalling" eId="container_2">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recalling</span> its previous resolutions concerning the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC),</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Reaffirming" eId="container_3">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Reaffirming</span> its strong commitment to the sovereignty, independence, unity and territorial integrity of the DRC as well as all States in the region and emphasising the need to respect fully the principles of non‑interference, good neighbourliness and regional cooperation,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Reiterating" eId="container_4">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Reiterating</span> the need to fully implement resolutions <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/2773(2025)">2773 (2025)</a> and <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/2808(2025)">2808 (2025)</a>, including the immediate cessation of hostilities, the unconditional withdrawal of Rwanda Defence Forces (RDF) from DRC territory, as well as the cessation of RDF support to M23 and of DRC military forces to specific armed groups, in particular the FDLR,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Expressing concern" eId="container_5">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Expressing concern</span> at the violations of the arms embargo documented in reports of the Group of Experts on the DRC (“the Group of Experts”) established pursuant to resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/1533(2004)">1533 (2004)</a> and extended pursuant to subsequent resolutions,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Expressing concern" eId="container_6">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Expressing concern</span> at the links, as documented by the Group of Experts, between the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) and international terrorist groups, which further exacerbate conflicts and contribute to undermining State authority, and pose a serious threat to civilians and regional stability,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Condemning" eId="container_7">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Condemning</span> all threats to the safety and security of peacekeepers and of United Nations personnel, as well as actions obstructing the implementation of the mandate of MONUSCO,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Reaffirming its concern" eId="container_8">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Reaffirming its concern</span> at the suffering of the civilian population of the country, at international humanitarian law violations and human rights violations and abuses, including those involving sexual and gender-based violence,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Further recognizing" eId="container_9">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Further recognizing</span> the role of natural resources linked to the conflict, including but not limited to gold, tin, tantalum, tungsten, and niobium, in funding illicit activities by armed groups in the DRC and the region, recalling the Group of Experts’ continued reporting on such illicit activities, and <span class="italic">underscoring</span> the importance for regional States to enhance transparency and traceability in natural resources exports,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Reiterating" eId="container_10">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Reiterating</span> that the armed and security forces of the Government of the DRC are exempt from the embargo on the supply of military equipment and assistance as indicated in SC/15689 agreed on 2 May 2024, and from any notification procedure as set out in paragraphs 1 and 2 below,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Determining" eId="container_11">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Determining</span> that the situation in the DRC continues to constitute a threat to international peace and security in the region,</p>
      </container>
      <container name="Acting" eId="container_12">
        <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Acting</span> under Chapter VII of the Charter of the United Nations,</p>
      </container>
    </preamble>
    <mainBody>
      <paragraph eId="para_13" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>1.</num>
        <content eId="para_13__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Decides</span> to renew until 1 July 2027 the measures as set out or extended in paragraphs 1 and 3 of resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/2783(2025)">2783 (2025)</a>, <span class="italic">decides</span> to extend, until 1 August 2027, the mandate of the Group of Experts as set forth in paragraph 6 of resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/2360(2017)">2360 (2017)</a> and paragraph 5 of resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/2783(2025)">2783 (2025)</a>, <span class="italic">reaffirms</span> paragraphs 4, 6 (as modified by the below reporting dates), 7 and 8 of resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/2783(2025)">2783 (2025)</a>, and <span class="italic">further decides</span> that the Group of Experts shall provide to the Council, after discussion with the Committee, a midterm report no later than 30 December 2026 and a final report no later than 15 June 2027;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_14" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>2.</num>
        <content eId="para_14__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Affirms</span> that paragraph 1 of this resolution is consistent with paragraphs 1 and 2 of resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/2667(2022)">2667 (2022)</a> and that the measures set forth in paragraph 1 of resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/1807(2008)">1807 (2008)</a> continue to apply to all non‑governmental entities and individuals operating in the territory of the DRC;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_16" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>3.</num>
        <content eId="para_16__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Calls</span> for enhanced cooperation between all States, particularly those in the region, and the Group of Experts, including for providing safe and unhindered access, in particular to persons, documents and sites necessary for the Group of Experts to execute its mandate, and <span class="italic">reaffirms</span> the importance of ensuring the safety and security of the members of the Group of Experts;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_19" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>4.</num>
        <content eId="para_19__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Decides</span> that the measures referred to in paragraph 3 of resolution <a href="https://docs.un.org/en/S/RES/2783(2025)">2783 (2025)</a> shall apply to armed groups (individuals and entities) as designated by the Committee for deliberate and grave obstruction of the implementation of MONUSCO’s mandate, including through denial of access, restrictions on freedom of movement, or interference with patrols and monitoring activities;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_23" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>5.</num>
        <content eId="para_23__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Recalls</span> the Secretary General’s commitment that the United Nations will do everything possible to ensure that the perpetrators of the killing of the two members of the Group of Experts and the four Congolese nationals accompanying them are brought to justice and stresses the importance of continued assistance, within existing resources, to the Democratic Republic of the Congo, with the ongoing prosecutions and national investigation, and to continue efforts to bring all those involved, including by planning, directing or sponsoring the killing, to justice;</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph eId="para_28" class="SingleTxt">
        <num>6.</num>
        <content eId="para_28__content">
          <p xml:space="preserve">	<span class="italic">Decides</span> to remain seized of the matter.</p>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
    </mainBody>
